gui.name: Name
gui.title: Title
guihint.avoidwater: If the NPC is following you, you can make them afraid of water (e.g., like an enderman)
guihint.leapontarget: The character can constantly leap at enemies with small jumps (imitating wolf behavior)
guihint.maxXP: Set the maximum amount of experience dropped by your NPC (if you set, for example, the number 50 everywhere, then you will always receive 50 XP)
guihint.minXP: Set the minimum amount of experience dropped by your NPC
guihint.movement: Adjust the parameters of your NPC's movement
guihint.movement.animation: Choose one of the provided animations so your character can sit, lie down, crawl, etc.
guihint.movement.isignore: Does your character rotate to you when you interact with it?
guihint.movement.movetype: Make the character either wander around or set your own route (you will need a <Npc Pather>)
guihint.movement.navigation: If you're creating a character that should swim or fly, this option will allow you to experiment with their behavior
guihint.movement.pos: You can shift the NPC left-right, forward-backward, and also raise them slightly upward
guihint.movement.rotation: Set a specific rotation angle for the NPC (e.g., if they are acting like a turret)
guihint.movement.speed: Set any speed for the NPC to make them slow or fast
guihint.npc2d3d: You can make the projectile volumetric or leave it flat
guihint.npcaccuracy: Here you can specify the shooting accuracy of your character (higher values result in more accurate ranged attacks)
guihint.npcaggrorange: Set the distance at which your character will notice a target
guihint.npcarrowsresist: Your character will be immune to arrows (higher values make arrows less effective against your NPC)
guihint.npcattackrange: If your character attacks with a long weapon, specify a value greater than 1 here (attack distance is measured in blocks)
guihint.npcattackspeed: Adjust the attack speed of your character (higher values result in slower attacks)
guihint.npcbossbar: If you are creating a boss, with this parameter you can display the health bar of your character
guihint.npcbossbarcolor: Change the color of the health bar of your character (first display it using the option on the left)
guihint.npcburnsinsun: Make your character burn in the sun, just like a zombie!
guihint.npcburstcount: With this parameter, you can make the character fire multiple projectiles separately
guihint.npcburstrate: If you want to simulate a machine gun, set the lowest possible value here (this also depends on delay parameters)
guihint.npccandrown: Does your character drown underwater? (this depends on whether your NPC can swim)
guihint.npccanswim: Make your character drown as if it is too heavy
guihint.npccape: If your character should have a cape, you can choose any of the provided options
guihint.npccobwebaffected: If you are creating a spider, this parameter will help you make the NPC pass through cobwebs without slowing down
guihint.npccombatregen: If your character should regenerate health during combat, specify any value here
guihint.npccreaturetype: Specify the creature type: if you are making a skeleton, for example, it's better to choose undead here so that the NPC has weaknesses to certain potions (a spider could have an arthropod type)
guihint.npcdamage: Set any value for the damage your character deals (damage does not depend on the weapon you give the NPC)
guihint.npcdoorinteract: How should the character interact with a door (for example break it, like a zombies)
guihint.npceffect: Choose any of the provided effects and set its duration in seconds
guihint.npceffectprojectile: You can give your projectile any effect on hitting a target (for example, poison, slowness, etc.)
guihint.npcexplodes: Attention! It is strongly not recommended to enable this option if you have not set the mobGriefing rule to false!
guihint.npcexplosionresist: Your character will be immune to explosive objects (higher values make explosions less effective against your NPC)
guihint.npcfiresound: What sound will play during shooting?
guihint.npcgravity: Set the gravity for your projectile (it can either fall at a constant rate or accelerate over time)
guihint.npcgroundsound: What sound will play after the projectile hits the ground?
guihint.npchasliving: If your character is a statue, this option can help you
guihint.npchealth: Set any value for the health of your character (floating point numbers are not supported)
guihint.npchealthregen: If your character should regenerate health after combat, specify any value here
guihint.npchidebody: U se this option to remove the body of the character after death
guihint.npchitbox: You can remove the hitbox of the character or add physics to it so that your character collides with objects
guihint.npchitsound: What sound will play after the projectile hits the target?
guihint.npcimmunetofire: You can make your character resistant to fire (even if you pour a bucket of lava on it, it won't burn)
guihint.npcknockback: The character can knock back the target if you specify a number no greater than 4
guihint.npcknockbackprojectile: For projectile power, you can set the knockback power on hitting a target
guihint.npcknockbackresist: Your character will be immune to knockback (higher values make the NPC less pushable)
guihint.npcmaxdelay: This parameter is similar to the low delay parameter (specify a number that will not be less than the minimum delay)
guihint.npcmeleeprops: This category allows you to change melee parameters (you can adjust damage, attack speed, etc.)
guihint.npcmeleeprops.peaceful: You have difficulty set to "Peaceful". The NPCs will be neutral to players (will not attack first)
guihint.npcmeleerange: At what distance in blocks will your character start attacking in melee?
guihint.npcmeleeresist: Your character will be immune to melee attacks (higher values make melee attacks less effective against your NPC)
guihint.npcmindelay: If you want to set the cooldown between shots fired by the character, specify a number here that will not exceed the maximum delay
guihint.npcmodel: You can choose one of the provided templates to quickly change your character appearance to any creature
guihint.npcmustseetarget: Is it mandatory for your character to see the target, or can it detect the target through walls?
guihint.npcname: Here you can write any name for your character
guihint.npcnofalldamage: You can also prevent the character from taking fall damage from great heights
guihint.npconfoundenemy: What action will your character take upon seeing a target? (for example, they may flee in panic)
guihint.npcoverlay: Change the texture of a specific part of the body (for example, you can change the eyes)
guihint.npcpotionimmune: This parameter ensures that your character does not receive any negative effects (such as poison, weakness, etc.)
guihint.npcprojectiletype: Adjust projectile properties to achieve the desired effect
guihint.npcrange: Specify the distance in blocks from which your character can shoot (this also depends on the aggro radius)
guihint.npcrangedprops: This category enables your character to perform ranged attacks
guihint.npcrangedprops.peaceful: You have difficulty set to "Peaceful". The NPCs' projectiles will not damage players
guihint.npcresistance: This category is for setting resistance to one of the four sources of damage
guihint.npcrespawn: Will your character respawn after death?
guihint.npcrespawntime: Specify the time after which the character should respawn each time (time is measured in seconds)
guihint.npcshelterfrom: This parameter will make your character seek shelter indoors (for example, during the night)
guihint.npcshootindirect: What shooting style does your character prefer? (for example, you can simulate a catapult)
guihint.npcshotcount: With this parameter, you can make the character fire more than one projectile simultaneously (if the value is greater than 1, it will resemble a shotgun)
guihint.npcsize: Specify any value that does not exceed 30 (you can configure the maximum value for this parameter in the mod configuration)
guihint.npcsizeprojectile: You can set any size for the projectile launched by the character (maximum value is 20)
guihint.npcspeedprojectile: Set the speed at which your projectile should fly (you can create bullet behavior)
guihint.npcstrength: Here you can adjust the damage that your projectile will deal
guihint.npctexture: Choose a texture that suits your character (you can upload your own textures via .minecraft/customnpcs folder)
guihint.npctint: Here you can change the tint of your character using the HEX color code (copy the HEX color without this symbol: #)
guihint.npctitle: If you want to specify the clan, class, or origin of the character, you can give it a prefix using this parameter
guihint.npctrailprojectile: If you are creating a magic projectile, this option can help you
guihint.npcvisible: This parameter allows you to make your character invisible or set conditions under which the character becomes invisible
guihint.npcwhileshooting: Will your character play aiming animation after seeing a target?
guihint.pickuptype: If the loot from the character is constantly scattering, it is recommended to set <Auto-Pickup>
guihint.return: Should the NPC return to their spawn point?
